Do battle in a ship's cargo hold with up to 30 players with buy zones for TDM, Bots, etc.
  • Main Deck has transparent, breakable grate sections (300 strength) for dynamic and surprising gameplay.
Multi-Range Engagement Strategies:
For long or short range weapons depending on your level in gungame. (Rush the main deck or go below/above to extend the round with longer range and strategic play)

Multi-Elevation Gameplay:
  1. Observation Decks and Platforms (Ramp & Ladder Access)
  2. Main Deck (Spawn Points)
  3. Gangway (Ramp & Fall Damage Access)
  4. Cargo Hold (Ladder and Increased Fall Damage Access)

Lighting:
  1. Main Deck is exposed to harsh sunlight causing realistic overexposure.
  2. Gangway is lit by some balanced, red emergency lighting.
  3. Cargo Hold has various traditional light sources to keep players identifiable, even in the shadows.

Gg_shade2 - by drimp

Here is the second version with all the things that people wanted and more:
- Added more detail and decals.
- Made stairs instead of the strange slope things.
- Added ropes in places.
- Made the sound inside the middle bit loader.
- Crates no longer in the ground.
- Other small things added. 

Please give constructive feedback and test it out in-game.

Known bugs: None. (If you know any please contact me.)

Story: In an abandoned factory after workers where taken hostage but saved by the counter terrorists the terrorists are going in for one last battle. The counter-terrorists must defend the factory at all cost. If lost the terrorists will use it as one of their secret hideouts.

Note: I did not add HDR because of bugs that made it so I could not build the cubemaps.
Includes a custom nav file for place names and so you can test gameplay with bots.
